      • generateTopologicalSortList

        public void generateTopologicalSortList()
        Generates a picklist using a pseudo depth-first topological sort, starting from the comparisons of one team and moving on to the nodes above/below it. Currently not very accurate or fast and results should NOT be used for creating an actual picklist. TODO Improve upon this method, possibly creating a way to insert new nodes BETWEEN existing ones e.g. If C is level 0, A is level 1, and A>B>C, we shouldn't force B to be either level 0 or 1, but have B be level 1 and promote all current nodes on level 1.

      • generateBogoCompareList

        public void generateBogoCompareList()
        Randomly generates many trees , then averages the ranks of teams in trees above a certain compliance percentage (threshold is a function of the number of teams). Needs many iterations, but the final result is 80-90% compliant, depending on the number of transitive contradictions. Running the method multiple times will lead to different lists, but the top and bottom tiers are generally consistent. TODO Improve the final result by taking more averages Note, however, that we may already be reaching the best possible trees

      • generateHeadToHeadList

        public void generateHeadToHeadList(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.Integer> orderedList,
                                   java.lang.String listTitle)
        Given a ranked list (generated from any method) of teams, swap teams if there are any head-to-head conflicts with adjacent teams. Only relies on comparisons, not another metric Essentially an implementation of bubble sort.
        Parameters:
        orderedList -

      • generateComparePointList

        public void generateComparePointList()
        Generates a list where a recommended (better) team gets +1 point for every comparison, while the worse team gets -1 point. Equal teams receive zero points. May be inaccurate due to one team playing consistently adjacent to better teams, etc. Not recommended for serious analysis.

      • generatePickPointList

        public void generatePickPointList()
        Generates a list that's the summation of all given pick points May be inaccurate due to some teams receiving more entries than others and the different rating scales of each scouts (some may tend to give higher ratings, etc.) Generally representative of robot ability. TODO Make the points an average rather than a summation
